section.def:
derat
                (滅鼠) means to control or kill the rodent vector
            of a disease;

disinfect
                (消毒) means to control, kill or eliminate the
            infectious agent of a disease;

disinsect
                (除蟲) means to control or kill the insect vector
            of a disease;

paragraph.content:
certifying that a person has been vaccinated or has received prophylaxis
                    against a disease in accordance with the International Health
                    Regulations;

the traveller fails to produce a certificate of vaccination or prophylaxis
                    for inspection as required by a health officer under section
                    19(1);
